@startuml evidence-overview
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ArrowColor #555555

title dev-workgraph — Evidence layer (§2–3)\n**evidence** (deterministic) + **summarize** (model)

legend top left
  |= Layer |= Trust |= Produced by |
  | **(D) Deterministic** | Evidence — always trustworthy | Pure code, no LLM |
  | **(M:c) Model** | Interpretation — may be wrong | Ollama **commitModel** |
  | **(H) Human / init** | Starting context — not proof | `init` → project.json |
endlegend

rectangle "**Preconditions**" #FFF8E1 {
  card "authors\nselectedAuthors[]" as AUTH
  card "init\nproject.json" as INIT
}

rectangle "**Stage 1 — evidence (D)**" #E8F5E9 {
  card "Git commits\n(selected authors)" as GIT
  card ".patch file\n(git show --format=fuller --find-renames)" as PATCH
  card "deterministic layer\nin .json" as DET
}

rectangle "**Stage 2 — summarize (M:c)**" as SUMBOX #FFF3E0 {
  card "model layer\nadded to same .json" as MOD
}

AUTH --> GIT : filter commits\nby author email
INIT ..> MOD : **project context block**\n(role, story, profile)\n→ interpretation only

GIT --> PATCH
GIT --> DET
PATCH --> MOD
DET --> MOD : metadata + areas\nfed into prompt\n(not overwritten)

note bottom of DET
  **On disk (append-only):**
  ~/.workgraph/data/repos/<repo-id>/commits/<ts>/<hash>.patch
  ~/.workgraph/data/repos/<repo-id>/commits/<ts>/<hash>.json
  At export: model = **null**
  **No signals. No questions.**
end note

note bottom of MOD
  Added by **summarize** (not evidence):
  • **signals** (technical / architecture / security)
  • summary, changeTypes, confidence, technologies
end note

@enduml


@startuml evidence-command
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #888888
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #E8F5E9

title **evidence** — Deterministic extraction (§2)\nNo LLM · no signals · no questions

start

:Resolve repository → repo-id;

:Load **selectedAuthors[]**\nfrom config (or --email override);

if (No authors?) then (yes)
  #Pink:Error — run `authors` first;
  stop
else (no)
endif

if (--period <id>?) then (yes)
  :Resolve [from, to) from config;\nFilter commits by **author timestamp** ∈ window;
  :Output dir:\nperiods/<id>/commits/;
else (no)
  :All-time commits;
  :Output dir:\ncommits/;
endif

:`getCommits(repo, emails, range)`\n**oldest first**, no merges;

partition "Per commit — **all deterministic (D)**" {
  if (patch + json exist?) then (yes)
    :Skip (append-only);
  else (no)
    :Write **<hash>.patch**\n`git show --format=fuller --find-renames`;
    note right
      Reproducible patch export
      Full commit metadata in patch header
    end note

    :Scan changed files + churn;

    partition "Noise filter (D)" {
      :Exclude paths matching noise rules;
      note right
        node_modules, dist, build, target,
        coverage, .next, *.min.js, *.map,
        package-lock.json, yarn.lock, pnpm-lock.yaml
        → **excludedFiles[]** (disclosed, not hidden)
      end note
    }

    partition "Area detection (D)" {
      :**area** = first path segment\n(e.g. backend/foo → backend;\nroot file → "(root)");
      note right: One file → one area;\ncommit.areas = unique set
    }

    :Build **deterministic** layer;
    note right
      changedFiles { added, deleted, modified, renamed }
      linesAdded / linesDeleted (churn, noise excluded)
      importantFolders[] (dirname of non-noise files)
      areas[] (top-level folders touched)
      excludedFiles[] (noise dropped)
    end note

    :Write **<hash>.json**;
    note right
      commitHash, timestamp, title, author
      deterministic: { … }
      **model: null**
    end note
  endif
}

#LightGreen:✅ Evidence extracted;

floating note left
  **May run without init** — deterministic layer is complete alone.
  **Requires authors** — only selected emails are exported.
  MVP minimum success: deterministic layer alone can pass criteria
  even if summarize never runs.
end note

stop

@enduml


@startuml evidence-summarize
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #888888
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFF3E0

title **summarize** — Model layer per commit (§3)\nOllama **commitModel** · signals appear here (not in evidence)

start

:List commits/**/*.json\n(skip if model present);

if (No exported commits?) then (yes)
  #Pink:Run `evidence` first;
  stop
else (no)
endif

:Pick **commitModel** (Ollama);

partition "Load init context" {
  :loadProjectContext(repo [, period]);
  :Build **project context block**;
  note right
    From **project.json** (init):
    • Developer role
    • profile.summary, domains, apparentStack, keyThemes
    • story.preparedContext
    • Ground interpretation — never inflate impact
  end note
  if (project.json missing?) then (yes)
    #FFF9C4:⚠️ Warn;\ncontinue with **empty** context;
  else (no)
  endif
  :system = projectContextBlock + COMMIT_SUMMARY_SYSTEM;
}

partition "Per pending commit (M:c)" {
  :Read deterministic layer + **.patch** file;
  :buildCommitUserPrompt(record, patch);
  note right
    User prompt (deterministic inputs):
    • commit title (context only — patch is truth)
    • areas, changedFiles, churn
    • patch diff (truncated if huge)
  end note

  :Ollama chatJson + JSON schema validation\n(up to 3 retries);

  :**enforceSignalReasons** (D post-process);
  note right
    Non-low signal without reason → demoted to **low**
    (prevents false precision)
  end note

  :Attach provenance (D):\nmodel, generatedAt, patchTruncated;

  :Write model layer into same .json;
}

#LightGreen:✅ Commit records updated;

stop

@enduml


@startuml evidence-commit-record
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam classBackgroundColor #FAFAFA

title Commit record after **evidence** — deterministic fields only\n`commits/<timestamp>/<hash>.json` · model = null

class "CommitRecord\n(written by evidence)" as CR #E8F5E9 {
  **Identity (D — from Git)**
  --
  commitHash : string
  timestamp : number
  title : string
  author : string
  --
  deterministic : DeterministicLayer
  model : **null**
}

class "DeterministicLayer\n**(D) evidence**" as DET #E8F5E9 {
  changedFiles.added[]
  changedFiles.deleted[]
  changedFiles.modified[]
  changedFiles.renamed[]
  --
  linesAdded : number
  linesDeleted : number
  --
  importantFolders[] : folders touched
  areas[] : top-level project areas
  excludedFiles[] : noise filter disclosure
}

class "Sidecar file" as PATCH #E3F2FD {
  <hash>.patch
  raw git show output
}

CR *-- DET
CR .. PATCH : same folder

note right of DET
  Computed without any model.
  Areas = first path segment rule.
  Noise excluded but listed in excludedFiles.
  **No signals. No questions.**
end note

note bottom of CR
  **summarize** (separate step) may later fill `model`
  on the same file — that is not part of evidence.
end note

@enduml


@startuml evidence-init-context
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false

title **evidence** does not use init context\n(init applies only to **summarize**, not to extraction)

package "init → project.json" #FFF8E1 {
  [role, story, profile] as INIT
}

package "**evidence (D)** — no init" #E8F5E9 {
  [Git log + selected authors] as GIT
  [patch via git show] as PATCH
  [deterministic layer] as DET
}

package "**summarize (M:c)** — uses init" #FFF3E0 {
  [project context block → system prompt] as BLOCK
  [model layer on same .json] as MOD
}

INIT -[hidden]-> GIT
GIT --> PATCH
PATCH --> DET

INIT ..> BLOCK : only here
DET ..> MOD : read by summarize,\nnot modified by init

note bottom of DET
  **evidence** runs with authors only.
  project.json is optional and ignored during extraction.
end note

@enduml


@startuml evidence-signals
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFF3E0

title **Signals** at commit level — appear in **summarize**, not in **evidence**

rectangle "Three coarse signals (M:c)\n**no numeric scores**" as SIG #FFF3E0 {
  card "**technicalSignal**\ndepth / complexity\nof the change" as TS
  card "**architectureSignal**\nstructure, boundaries,\nmodules, system design" as AS
  card "**securitySignal**\nauthn, authz, identity,\ndata protection, permissions" as SS
}

rectangle "Rules" as RULES {
  card "Each value: **low | medium | high**" as R1
  card "Non-low **requires** one-line\n**signalReasons.*** grounded in patch" as R2
  card "**enforceSignalReasons (D):**\nsignal without reason → **low**" as R3
}

SIG --> RULES

rectangle "Downstream (later stages)" as DOWN #E3F2FD {
  card "commit-group **groups.tiers**\n(D partition from per-commit signals)" as TIER
  card "group / report fold\naggregates signals" as AGG
}

SIG --> DOWN

note bottom
  **evidence** writes none of this — only patch + deterministic JSON.
  Signals are produced later by **summarize** (commitModel).
end note

@enduml


@startuml evidence-sequence
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false

title Sequence — **evidence** (deterministic only)

actor "Developer" as DEV
participant "Git repo" as GIT
database "config.json\nauthors" as CFG
participant "**evidence**\n(D)" as EVID
database "commits/<ts>/\n.hash.patch + .json" as DISK

DEV -> EVID : dev-workgraph evidence ./repo\n[--period]

EVID -> CFG : selectedAuthors[]
EVID -> GIT : log + show patches\n(filter by email [, date window])

loop each commit (oldest first)
  EVID -> EVID : noise filter, areas, churn\nbuildDeterministic()
  EVID -> DISK : write .patch + .json\n(deterministic + **model: null**)
end

EVID --> DEV : extracted / skipped counts

note over DISK
  No init, no Ollama, no signals, no questions.
  **summarize** is a separate command on these files.
end note

@enduml


@startuml evidence-trust-boundary
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false

title Trust boundary — what **evidence** produces (§2)

legend left
  **evidence (D) outputs**
  ----
  .patch file — git show --format=fuller --find-renames
  .json identity — commitHash, timestamp, title, author
  .json deterministic — changedFiles, linesAdded/Deleted
  .json deterministic — importantFolders, areas, excludedFiles
  .json model — **null** (not written by evidence)
endlegend

floating note left
  Interpretation (summary, signals, changeTypes, …) is added later
  by **summarize** on the same file. **evidence** alone is complete evidence.
end note

@enduml
